title: Jordan Merlin-Jones - "Out Of Hiding" - A Senior Project Vocal Recital - Studio Mix
description:
Friday, June 3rd, 2016 - Sidwell Friends School - RLS Meeting House.
Mixed by Trevor Higgins @ Potomac Sound LLC - www.potomacsound.com
YouTube Video Footage: http://bit.ly/1UBBX6j

GUESTS MUSICIANS:

Keelin Quirk - Violin (1,5,8-9)
Caroline Beckman - Cello (1,5,8-9)
Spenser Hyun - Trumpet (2), Drums (3), Keyboards (7) 
Ananth Shastri - Flute (3,7)
Ana Danao-Schroeder - Bass (3,7)
Sam Panner ‚Äì Guitar (3), Drums (7)
Maya Robnett - Keyboards (3,7)
Ben Lee - Guitar (7)
Avery Schonberger - Piano (7)
Nicholas Adeyi - Violin (10)
David Merlin-Jones - Piano (1-3, 5-6, 8) Tenor Saxophone (7), Drums (9-10)
John Touchton - Piano (9,11)
Jerome Walker - Vocals, Piano (10)
Imani Pugh - Vocals (3,7)
Mattias Lundberg - Vocals, Guitar (4)
Moses Feldman - Vocals (8)
Amelia Getahun-Hawkins - Vocals (7)

Jordan would like to thank her senior project advisor, John Touchton, who has not only been extraordinarily supportive through the senior project process, but also over the last four years as an educator and friend. She would like to thank her dad, David Merlin-Jones, for being the best accompanist a girl could ask for - thanks for playing piano of all these years and for helping her to grow into the artist and young woman she is today. Last but not least, a special thank you to Caroline Holtz, who was Jordan's choral director in and outside of Sidwell from 5th-8th grade, and to John Elko, Ed Crow, and Anne Stone Crow for sharing their knowledge, wisdom, kindness and compassion with her throughout their time together on and off the stage.

Jordan Merlin-Jones has been singing in choral settings - inside and outside of Sidwell Friends - since pre-kindergarten. Her involvement in multiple middle school choral ensembles later inspired her to start her own a cappella groups in the 8th and 9th grades. Jordan joined the Sidwell Friends Chamber Chorus in her sophomore year, and was elected as the Chorus Co-president for the 2015-2016 academic year alongside Mattias Lundberg '16. When she entered the upper school, her career as a solo performer grew as she took advantage of the performance opportunities that Arts Guild, a cappella and theater provided. Jordan has been in 7 Sidwell productions; even though she arrived late on the theater scene, she has found her niche and is extraordinarily passionate about connecting with people through her craft. Jordan will be attending Emerson College for Theater and Performance in the fall.

title: THE MATRIX - Work in progress - THE ENDLESS VIEW
description:
Raccolta di demo e registrazioni varie inerenti al progetto "The Matrix", un concept album nato dai testi di Andrea Salerno. Una prima versione dell'album sarebbe dovuta uscire nel 2017, tra il 2018 e il 2019 √® stato riveduto, purtroppo ad oggi √® rimasto inedito. Andrea Salerno stesso ha pubblicato delle demo alternative degli stessi pezzi (eccetto "Environment"), in cui non sono presenti gli altri componenti del gruppo oltre lui e me, perch√© a suo tempo non avevamo i mezzi per registrare con la band al completo in casa. Ci√≤ che troverete qui √® la ricostruzione pi√π fedele possibile a ci√≤ che doveva essere il prodotto finito con la formazione pi√π caratteristica dei The Endless View, che nulla toglie ai caricamenti di Andrea Salerno gi√† pubblicati. La seguente playlist contiene sia registrazioni in casa che in sala prove, dunque, chiedo scusa per la qualit√† audio non sempre eccellente.

I The Endless View sono (in ordine alfabetico):
Luca Agosta: voce
Gabriele Notarrigo: basso
Giuseppe Platania: batteria
Andrea Salerno: voce, chitarre, basso e produzione
Carmelo Santangelo: piano digitale e tastiere

Scaletta:
1. I Am the Matrix (Ouverture) - musica di Carmelo Santangelo
2. Login (Entrance) - musica di Andrea Salerno
3. Welcome to the Matrix - musica di A. Salerno & C. Santangelo
4. Alternate View - musica di Andrea Salerno
5. Environment - musica di A. Salerno & C. Santangelo
6. Don't Leave Me Now - musica di Andrea Salerno
7. Caustic Love - musica di A. Salerno & C. Santangelo
8. The Matrix - musica di Andrea Salerno
9. The Other Side - musica di A. Salerno & C. Santangelo
10. Psychedelic Dream - musica di A. Salerno, C. Santangelo & G. Platania
11. Rebirth/Outside the Matrix - musica di G. Platania, G. Notarrigo, A. Salerno & C. Santangelo

Tutti i testi sono di Andrea Salerno

Nota: Mi sono permesso di caricare queste registrazioni visto che, a suo tempo, il progetto fu concepito per essere reso pubblico con questa formazione e soprattutto dal momento in cui versioni alternative di questi pezzi sono gi√† presenti su SoundCloud. Ci tengo a precisare, inoltre, che non guadagno nulla da questo caricamento.

title: Merlowe and The dry Tear
description:
"Merlowe and The dry Tear" is the the third release by Merlowe & The Dry Tear and continues Monk Owen's "accidental" exploration of music.

"Accidental"? Here's the story:

"The Accidental Studio Pro" - I walked into my first recording studio at 14 and realized that with my musical knowledge and a little production technique I could create sounds that went way beyond teenage pop and almost immediately became a studio musician. The studio folks found out that I could play multiple instruments so I became part of the in-house studio band by filling in on the instrument that no one else around that day could play. I honed my skills playing bass, keyboard, and guitars on dozens of demos. While doing demo sessions one day, the hired mixer got so frustrated because of how long the session was taking he left and told me I could take over if I wanted to. I did and never looked back.

"The Accidental Artist" - Because I‚Äôd accidently learned how to do all those things for all the wrong reasons I decided to start recording what I wanted to do musically for all the right reasons.
tag_list: "Merlowe & the Dry Tear" "Third album" "Monk Owen" "The Accidental Studio Pro" "The Accidental Artist" "Pep Ventura"
